CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 3, 1946, pg. 8, reads: "Lovely Wedding for Pretty Dorothy Jackson - When Miss Dorothy Jackson was married to Wayne Walker in a charming ceremony held in home of Mrs. Samuel Wynn, the wedding party was a thing of beauty. Pictured are Charlotte Bishop and Wyonella Croft, bridesmaids; Marjorie Jackson, maid of honor; the bride and groom, and usher, Bobby Hall; best man, Harry Walker; usher, Don Jackson, and flower girl, Linda Jackson."
TitMainTitle: Group of men and women gathered around, including groom Wayne Walker wearing tuxedo, and bride Dorothy Jackson wearing veil, in interior with venetian blinds and sconce on wall, Jackson-Walker wedding
